missionEventData.data2: In the far reaches of the Outer Rim a rebellion is forming. A rebel cell led by the frigate Redemption and ace pilot Keyan Farlander have been striking back against the evil galactic empire. But the Emperor is at the height of his power, and even now he is marshalling his forces at the edge of the mid-rim. But help has come from the most unlikely of places. The captain of an imperial corvette has sent the rebel freedom fighters a secret message, he wishes to defect...

missionEventData.data1: The Sullustan leadership has agreed to support the Alliance on the condition that their technical staff are safely returned. The meeting is being held at a secret location in the Sullust system. Your job is to protect the Sullustan leadership and their staff at all costs. Our security for this meeting was the tightest ever, but we can never underestimate the capabilities of Imperial spies!
Red Squadron head to the jump point immediately. The Bixby will follow.
I'm reading several ships emerging from Hyperspace. It's the Sullustan contingent.
This the Alliance Corvette Bixby hailing Sullustian Frigate. Transport Tector is ready to commence the transfer of prisoners.
Acknowledged Bixby. Transport Cosof stands ready to receive.
It's the Invincible. All ships take evasive action. Tector abandon the transfer.
We don't have a choice lieutenant. The Bixby can't hold out against a Star Destroyer!
Five minutes sir! That's all we need...
Okay, Red Squadon engage those Ties. Tector, you have three minutes to complete the transfer.
There not giving up. I'm reading a squadron of Tie Bombers launching.
I'm detecting more fighters launching from the Invincible.
Looks like we exhausted the Invincible. She's leaving the system.
Half the prisoners have been transferred.
Okay. This is the Bixby. All ships prepared to leave the system.
Red Squadron, keep those fighters off our back until all ships have jumped.
Thanks for the cover Red Squadron. See you on the other side. Bixby out.
Okay Red Squadron. Drop your targets and make a break for the jump point.
Okay Red Squadron. Return to the jump point.
